                "name": "Player Core pg. 11",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "name": "Player Core",
              "page": 11,
              "type": "source"
            }
          ],
          "text": "Something of uncommon rarity requires special training or comes from a particular culture or part of the world. Some character choices give access to uncommon options, and the GM can choose to allow access for anyone. Less is known about uncommon creatures than common creatures. They typically can't be summoned. The DC of Recall Knowledge checks related to these creature is increased by 2.",
          "type": "trait"
        },
        {
          "classes": [
            "size"
          ],
          "edition": "legacy",
          "game-id": "e5efc5cd9e470cd9d2f53049190af83d",
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "name": "Gargantuan",
          "sources": [
            {
              "errata": {
                "alt": "2.0",
                "game-obj": "Sources",
                "name": "2.0",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "link": {
                "alt": "Core Rulebook pg. 474",
                "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01y0k?Pathfinder-Core-Rulebook",
                "name": "Core Rulebook pg. 474",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "name": "Core Rulebook",
              "page": 474,
              "type": "source"
            }
          ],
          "text": "*Space:* 20 feet or more, *Reach (Tall):* 20 feet, *Reach (Long):* 15 feet",
          "type": "trait"
        },
        {
          "alternate_link": {
            "alternate_type": "legacy",
            "aonid": 108,
            "game-obj": "Traits",
            "type": "alternate_link"
          },
          "classes": [
            "monsters"
          ],
          "edition": "remastered",
          "game-id": "1debc9c19f9ffadf57ee0ebf1bc785cb",
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "name": "Mindless",
          "sources": [
            {
              "errata": {
                "alt": "2.0",
                "aonid": 216,
                "game-obj": "Sources",
                "name": "2.0",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "link": {
                "alt": "Player Core pg. 458",
                "aonid": 216,
                "game-obj": "Sources",
                "name": "Player Core pg. 458",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "name": "Player Core",
              "page": 458,
              "type": "source"
            }
          ],
          "text": "A mindless creature has either programmed or rudimentary mental attributes. Most, if not all, of their mental attribute modifiers are \u20135. They are immune to all mental effects.",
          "type": "trait"
        },
        {
          "alternate_link": {
            "alternate_type": "legacy",
            "aonid": 367,
            "game-obj": "Traits",
            "type": "alternate_link"
          },
          "classes": [
            "monsters"
          ],
          "edition": "remastered",
          "game-id": "2d407154112121f24c49d97c89d90b55",
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "links": [
            {
              "alt": "troop defenses",
              "aonid": 86,
              "game-obj": "MonsterAbilities",
              "name": "troop defenses",
              "type": "link"
            },
            {
              "alt": "troop movement",
              "aonid": 85,
              "game-obj": "MonsterAbilities",
              "name": "troop movement",
              "type": "link"
            }
          ],
          "name": "Troop",
          "sources": [
            {
              "link": {
                "alt": "NPC Core pg. 238",
                "aonid": 236,
                "game-obj": "Sources",
                "name": "NPC Core pg. 238",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "name": "NPC Core",
              "page": 238,
              "type": "source"
            }
          ],
          "text": "A troop is an organized collection of component creatures, typically Small or Medium in size, working as a cohesive whole. Over the course of enough attacks and downed comrades, troops shrink in size. A troop typically has the troop defenses and troop movement abilities, and most troops have weaknesses to area damage and splash damage. Because they consist of multiple discrete creatures, they can't be summoned.",
          "type": "trait"
        },
        {
          "alternate_link": {
            "alternate_type": "legacy",
            "aonid": 160,
            "game-obj": "Traits",
            "type": "alternate_link"
          },
          "classes": [
            "creature_type"
          ],
          "edition": "remastered",
          "game-id": "20f6f5f93a453f3006eb194c6d712042",
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "name": "Undead",
          "sources": [
            {
              "errata": {
                "alt": "2.0",
                "aonid": 216,
                "game-obj": "Sources",
                "name": "2.0",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "link": {
                "alt": "Player Core pg. 462",
                "aonid": 216,
                "game-obj": "Sources",
                "name": "Player Core pg. 462",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "name": "Player Core",
              "page": 462,
              "type": "source"
            }
          ],
          "text": "Once living, these creatures were infused after death with void energy and soul-corrupting unholy magic. When reduced to 0 Hit Points, an undead creature is destroyed. Undead creatures are damaged by vitality energy and are healed by void energy, and don\u2019t benefit from healing vitality effects.",
          "type": "trait"
        },
        {
          "classes": [
            "monsters"
          ],
          "edition": "remastered",
          "game-id": "6309897c89780f17449b984cbb6d26cb",
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "links": [
            {
              "alt": "holy",
              "aonid": 517,
              "game-obj": "Traits",
              "name": "holy",
              "type": "link"
            }
          ],
          "name": "Unholy",
          "sources": [
            {
              "errata": {
                "alt": "2.0",
                "aonid": 216,
                "game-obj": "Sources",
                "name": "2.0",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "link": {
                "alt": "Player Core pg. 462",
                "aonid": 216,
                "game-obj": "Sources",
                "name": "Player Core pg. 462",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "name": "Player Core",
              "page": 462,
              "type": "source"
            }
          ],
          "text": "Effects with the unholy trait are tied to powerful magical forces of cruelty and sin. They often have stronger effects on holy creatures. Creatures with this trait are strongly devoted to unholy causes, and often have weakness to holy. If a creature with weakness to unholy uses an unholy item or effect, it takes damage from its weakness.",
          "type": "trait"
        }
      ],
      "type": "stat_block_section"
    },
    "defense": {
      "ac": {
        "subtype": "armor_class",
        "type": "stat_block_section",
        "value": 42
      },
      "automatic_abilities": [
        {
          "ability_type": "automatic",
          "links": [
            {
              "alt": "skeletons",
              "aonid": 472,
              "game-obj": "MonsterFamilies",
              "name": "skeletons",
              "type": "link"
            },
            {
              "alt": "zombies",
              "aonid": 487,
              "game-obj": "MonsterFamilies",
              "name": "zombies",
